    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-03-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="156"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Stevens</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-03-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received with great appreciation the copy
                    of the resolutions of February 4, 1891, of the Honolulu Chamber of Commerce
                    which accompany your No. 19 of 16th ultimo, relating to the late visit of His
                    Majesty King Kalakaua to this country, and to his lamented death; as also to the
                    attention paid him while here and the solemn conveyance of his remains by one of
                    our war-ships, from California to Honolulu.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
